  "text": "Sprague-Dawley rats. Primary BMSCs were isolated and cultured, as described previously [CITATION_1] . The harvested cells were centrifuged at 500 x g for 10 min at 4˚C and then resuspended in complete Dulbecco's modified Eagle's medium (DMEM)/F-12 with 10% fetal bovine serum (FBS), 100 µg/ml streptomycin and 100 U/ml penicillin (all purchased from Gibco Life Technologies, Carlsbad, CA, USA). Cells at passage 3 were subjected to flow cytometric analysis (Cytomics FC500; Beckman Coulter, Brea, CA, USA) to assess the expression of the surface markers, cluster of differentiation 29 (CD29), CD90, CD31 and CD45. The osteogenic and adipogenic differentiation potentials of the cells were also assessed by Alizarin red staining (Beyotime Institute of Biotechnology, Haimen, China) and Oil Red O staining (Beyotime Institute of Biotechnology).",
  "correct_citation": {
